15/06/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- A Turkish soldier and a Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) member reportedly died Saturday (June 13th) during clashes near the border with Iraq, media reported Sunday, citing Turkish security sources. The fighting reportedly broke out in a mountainous region around the town of Yuksekova. (Milliyet, Radikal, Cumhuriyet - 15/06/09, Anadolu news agency, CNNTurk, Hurriyet, Dogan news agency, AFP, Reuters, Xinhua - 14/06/09)
